\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {7}{\ignorespaces GENIUS Act quantitative counterfactual. Under reserve composition rules (T-bills, central bank reserves, Treasury-backed repos), Circle's \$3.3B held at SVB would have been in instruments immune to bank failure, eliminating the reserve lock-up that caused the USDC de-peg. Counterfactual $D_t$ is bounded by the pre-crisis level.}}{10}{table.7}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:genius_cf}{{7}{10}{GENIUS Act quantitative counterfactual. Under reserve composition rules (T-bills, central bank reserves, Treasury-backed repos), Circle's \$3.3B held at SVB would have been in instruments immune to bank failure, eliminating the reserve lock-up that caused the USDC de-peg. Counterfactual $D_t$ is bounded by the pre-crisis level}{table.7}{}}
